radiographic_examinations.findings: Reportedly normal, no evidence of malformation or other significant abnormalities.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Eighteen months after initial evaluation, cranial MRI revealed mild cerebral and cerebellar atrophy and mild periventricular hyperintensities.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Diffuse, largely symmetric, supratentorial and cerebellar atrophy. Involvement of the frontal and parietal lobes and superior vermis.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Atrophy involves increased volume loss over time when compared to control.
